Forked / vendored third-party components
================================================================================

This project depends on the following third-party software components, each
maintained as a separate fork with nvsnap-specific patches. Their original
licenses apply.

----
CRIU (Checkpoint/Restore In Userspace)
  Upstream: https://github.com/checkpoint-restore/criu
  NvSnap fork: maintained by the NvSnap project (branch criu-dev)
  License: GPL-2.0 (for the userspace tool); LGPL-2.1 (for the libcriu/libsoccr
           libraries); see the upstream LICENSE files for the authoritative
           per-file licensing.

----
uvloop
  Upstream: https://github.com/MagicStack/uvloop
  NvSnap fork: maintained by the NvSnap project
  License: Apache-2.0 / MIT (dual license; see upstream LICENSE-APACHE and
           LICENSE-MIT).

----
libuv
  Upstream: https://github.com/libuv/libuv
  NvSnap fork: maintained by the NvSnap project
  License: MIT (see upstream LICENSE).

----
libzmq (ZeroMQ)
  Upstream: https://github.com/zeromq/libzmq
  NvSnap fork: maintained by the NvSnap project
  License: MPL-2.0 (see upstream LICENSE).

----
pyzmq
  Upstream: https://github.com/zeromq/pyzmq
  NvSnap build artifact only (rebuilt from upstream against the nvsnap libzmq fork)
  License: BSD-3-Clause (see upstream LICENSE.md).

----
go-criu
  Upstream: https://github.com/checkpoint-restore/go-criu
  NvSnap fork: maintained by the NvSnap project
  License: Apache-2.0 (see upstream LICENSE).

----
NVIDIA cuda-checkpoint
  Upstream: distributed with NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit
  Used as a binary dependency for GPU state checkpoint/restore.
  License: subject to the NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit license.

